In contrast to earlier studies, the recovery of a mitogenomic
dataset allowed us to generate a robust phylogeny and an
assessment of divergence times among lineages. This
showed that the most recent female common ancestor of
the arctic fox probably lived less than 100 000 BP (figure 2).
